        "created_at": "2021-09-22T20:54:46.612Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019m really new to FDB so sorry in advance if my question doesn\u2019t make sense. Is there a way to use two disks on a single machine for FDB io/storage? I have a machine that has two ephemeral disks and io is limited to the disk size so I want to use both disks to use all io available on the virtual machine.<br>\nIn the <code>foundationdb.conf</code> the <code>datadir</code> specifies the data location but not sure how to provide two locations in this case.</p>",
